# Lie.Branching

Branching rule interfaces.

A branching rule describes how a representation of a Lie algebra 𝔤 decomposes
under restriction to a subalgebra 𝔥 ⊂ 𝔤.

Key branching chains relevant to Standard Model physics:
  E₈ ⊃ E₆ × SU(3)
  E₈ ⊃ SO(16)
  E₈ ⊃ E₇ × SU(2)
  E₆ ⊃ SO(10) × U(1)
  SO(10) ⊃ SU(5) × U(1)
  SU(5) ⊃ SU(3) × SU(2) × U(1)  (Standard Model gauge group)

Oracle backends: LieART, SageMath Weyl character ring.
All branching rules should be cross-checked against at least one CAS oracle.

Status: stub — branching rule data structures to be defined.
-/

